Dataset.
There are two real-world datasets derived from location-based social media platforms for the experiments: NYC(Foursquare-NYC) and TKY (Foursquare-TKY) are. NYC contains 103,941 check-ins (check in records?)collected from 1,048 users across 4,981 POIs. TKY includes 405,000 check-ins from 2,282 users across 7,833 POIs. Both datasets are collected over approximately from April 2012 to February 2013 as listed in Table 2.

Implementation Details
There are five experiments conducted and averaged the results for each dataset as listed in Table 3. The temperature of all LLMs is set at 0 for comparison. The datasets preprocessing is managed by DataAgent, and are partitioned into training, validation, and test sets with a ratio of 8:1:1. Notably, only the final check-in record of each trajectory is assessed in the validation and test sets.

MAS4POI integrates six LLMs across three datasets experiments results are listed in Table  3.

The overlap in POI trajectories among different users allows the Analyst to support the structured check-in records constructed by the DataAgent to identify suitable candidate POIs, even if an inactive user’s own trajectory is limited i.e. users often visit CaffeeShop or PublicTransitStations at weekday mornings.
